text: Follow up #2: The above was remiss in not acknowledging the incredible work of @Tuliodna, @ceri_news, @nicd_sa, @nhls_sa in generating and sharing sequence data on BA.4 and BA.5 in South Africa. They've been absolutely essential throughout the pandemic. https://t.co/Xvz6xvkqtX

@IanFelipeSays Over 50 years since emergence of H3N2 influenza we're discussing clades 3C.2a, 3C.3a, 3C.3a1, etc... https://t.co/GRMfTSOqt7 Seasonal coronaviruses haven't been studied as intensively and there hasn't been a reason to need a detailed nomenclature.

Given one "Omicron-like" event happening in 2.35 years of pandemic, it's not at all clear how frequent these events will be going forward, where this observation is compatible with a true underlying rate of "Omicron-like" events every 1.5 years or every 10.5 years (80% CI). 10/13 https://t.co/BX2ztFLbpp
